消費者間接支持動物實驗?
photo: PETA
動物實驗儘管現今的科技日新月異，實驗動物的虐待仍是動物們目前面臨到最大的問題。根據統計，每年至少約有1-1.25億的動物被用來做實驗動物，狗、貓、兔子、天竺鼠、小白鼠、豬、非人類靈長類、鳥、兩棲類及魚類皆被用來做實驗。在實驗中牠們被剝奪所有對牠們而言重要且在自然環境中生長應有的要素，承受著極大的痛苦及精神上的壓力。目的為何? 實驗動物被用來做為化妝品、家庭用品、藥物、殺蟲劑、食品添加物及疫苗的測試，然而有些卻只是為了做研究。小白鼠的神經系統與人類相似，可以感受到疼痛、害怕、寂寞及愛護其家庭。因此為了在牠們身上做心理相關的實驗，會利用下毒及燒傷牠們的方式以使其感到焦慮、沮喪或害怕及沒有希望。兔子是極為敏感的動物，可以感受到痛苦的程度與人類相像。牠們被用來做為化妝品、肥皂、清潔劑的測試，更甚者，將液體滴入牠們的眼中造成其眼睛腫脹、產生分泌物、流血、失明或疼痛。牠們也被用來做為毒性測試，將牠們的毛髮剃掉後把化學物質塗抹在其皮膚上長達數週之久且不給予任何的止痛劑。然而，實驗完成後每一隻兔子卻逃不過被撲殺的命運。猴子是相當聰明、敏感及在家庭結構上與人類非常相近的生物。牠們被用來做為藥物的測試 —利用實驗用的軟管直接伸入牠們的喉嚨裡或插入其鼻中將藥物註入牠們的體內，這樣的方式對於預測人類用藥的安全與否其實有90%是失敗的。狗是相當聰明、忠誠及群居的動物，跟人一樣可感受到痛苦及害怕。牠們被用來做為毒物的測試－將藥物、化學物品及清潔劑註入其體內以測試中毒的速度，而牠們將會緩慢的死去。豬是極為聰明且社會化的動物。牠們被用來測試化學物品的毒性作用 —在沒有施予任何止痛藥的狀況之下，牠們部分的皮膚會被化學物品灼傷及拔除。結果為何?動物實驗不僅極為殘忍且不人道，其實也相當的不準確。毒物的毒性測試，對於皮膚及眼部的刺激或藥物的效用僅能代表在該測試的動物身上所造成的影響，並不能用來推斷對於人類的效果。況且，很多在動物實驗上呈陽性反應，在人類身上是呈現陰性的結果。近幾年來，已發展出越來越多更可靠、快速且較動物實驗便宜的試驗方式，例如皮膚細胞的培養及以電腦模擬的方式來做測試，但令人難過的是全球仍有許多地方正在進行著不文明的動物實驗。我們能做些甚麼?尋找leaping bunny(跳躍的兔子)，那些沒有利用殘忍的動物實驗所製造出來的產品上會有標示leaping bunny或未使用動物實驗的符號，而我們可以選擇購買這些產品。做為一個有同情心的購買者，上網找出那些仍在做動物實驗的公司並且停止購買他們的產品。將這些文字分享給他人，仍有許多人尚未察覺他們所購買的產品其實是利用動物實驗所製造出來的。說出你的想法，寫信告訴那些仍在進行動物實驗的公司，告訴他們除非停止動物實驗，否則你將不會再繼續支持他們的產品。Animal ExperimentationDespite all of our advances in the modern world of science, animal abuse in labs is still one of the biggest problems facing animals today.  A low estimate of 100-125 million animals are tested on globally each year.  Dogs, cats, rabbits, guinea pigs, mice, pigs, non-human primates, birds, amphibians and fish are all experimented on.  During the experiments they are deprived of everything that is natural and important to them, suffer excruciating pain and mental distress.For what?Animals are used to test cosmetics, household products, drugs, pesticides, food additives, vaccines and just for the sake of research.Mice have very similar nervous systems to humans and can feel pain, fear, loneliness and love their families.They are poisoned, burned and given psychological tests to make them feel anxiety, depression and helplessness.Rabbits are sentient animals that have the same ability to feel pain as we do.They are used to test makeup, soap, cleaners and more by dripping liquids into their eyes, which causes swelling, discharge, bleeding, blindness and pain. They are used to test toxicity by shaving off their fur and applying chemicals to their skin for weeks without any painkillers. After each rabbit’s test is finished they are killed.Monkeys are very intelligent, sensitive and family oriented animals, very similar to humans.They are used to test drugs - tubes are put down their throats or up their noses and drugs are pumped into their bodies -this method has a 90% failure rate in predicting safety for humans.Dogs are smart, loving, pack animals who can feel pain and fear just as humans do.They are used to test toxicity: drugs, chemicals and cleaners are pumped into their bodies to measure toxicity rates - from which they will slowly die.Pigs are extremely intelligent social animals. They are used to test toxic effects of chemicals- parts of their skin is burned and removed without any painkillers.Results?Not only is animal testing inhumane and cruel, it is highly inaccurate.  The testing of toxicity levels, skin and eye irritants or drug effectiveness on animals is only relevant to the animal it’s tested on and cannot be extrapolated to humans.   Moreover, test that have positive results in animals often show negative results in humans.  In recent years more reliable, faster and less expensive non- animal testing methods have been developed such as skin cultures and computer models.  Sadly barbaric animal testing is still going on around the world today.

What can we do?

Look for the leaping bunny. Products that are NOT tested on animals will have the leaping bunny or cruelty free logo on it.  Purchase these products rather than others.Be a compassionate shopper. Do your research online to find companies that practice animal testing and stop supporting them.Spread the word. Many people are still unaware that products they use are tested on animals. Voice your concern.  Write to companies that do animal experiments to tell them you won’t support them until they abolish animal testing.


 Cruelty Free Companies (PETA)File Size:  352 kbFile Type:   pdf下載檔案

















